  <section>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para>Asynchronous operations ("tasks") immediately return HTTP
    <computeroutput>202 Accepted</computeroutput> with a
    <computeroutput>Location:</computeroutput> header pointing to a simple
    task [sub]resource. This allows tasks to be monitored
    (<computeroutput>GET</computeroutput>), updated
    (<computeroutput>PUT</computeroutput>) and canceled
    (<computeroutput>DELETE</computeroutput>). Completed tasks
    <emphasis>may</emphasis> be deleted immediately, after a reasonable period
    of time (allowing clients to retrieve status) or retained indefinitely for
    audit purposes.</para>

    <para>The collection of tasks for a given resource (including the
    entry-point itself for global tasks) is advertised under the
    <computeroutput>http://purl.org/occi#tasks</computeroutput> link relation
    and new tasks should be submitted via HTTP
    <computeroutput>POST</computeroutput> to the supplied
    <computeroutput>href</computeroutput>.</para>

